        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 29 at 8:14PM CDT until August 29 at 9:15PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>SVRAMA

The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Oldham County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Northwestern Deaf Smith County in the Panhandle of Texas...
West central Moore County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Hartley County in the Panhandle of Texas...

* Until 915 PM CDT.

* At 814 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 12 miles southwest of Dalhart to 9 miles east of
Romero to 6 miles south of Nara Visa, moving south at 40 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.

* Locations impacted include...
Hartley, Channing, Adrian, Glenrio, and Romero.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with these storms, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
